### Resolve Conflicts in RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/local-first-future.md

The resolve function handles conflict resolution, which can be asynchronous, allowing for UI interactions. The example provided implements a 'first-on-server-wins' strategy by returning the server's state. Custom handlers can merge properties or implement 'last-write-wins'.

```javascript
async resolve(i) {
    /**
     * In this example we drop the local state and use the server-state.
     * This basically implements a "first-on-server-wins" strategy.
     * 
     * In your custom conflict handler you could want to merge properties
     * of the i.realMasterState, i.assumedMasterState and i.newDocumentState
     * or return i.newDocumentState to have a "last-write-wins" strategy.
     */
    return i.realMasterState;
}
```

