### Event Sourcing Example for RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/downsides-of-offline-first.md

Demonstrates the 'everything is a delta' or event sourcing strategy where each change is recorded as a new document rather than modifying existing ones. This approach inherently avoids conflicts by maintaining an append-only log of all events leading to the current state. It's suitable for scenarios like tracking financial transactions where historical data is crucial.

```typescript
{
  id: new Date().toJSON(),
  change: 100
} // balance increased by $100
{
  id: new Date().toJSON(),
  change: -50
} // balance decreased by $50
{
  id: new Date().toJSON(),
  change: 200
} // balance increased by $200
```

