### RxDB Custom Conflict Handler Example

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/local-first-future.md

Demonstrates a custom conflict handler function for RxDB, illustrating how to implement client-side merge logic for data synchronization. This approach allows developers to define specific strategies for reconciling divergent data states when conflicts arise during synchronization, such as comparing document states for equality.

```typescript
import { deepEqual } from 'rxdb/plugins/utils';
export const myConflictHandler = {
    /**
     * @param {import('rxdb/dist/types/rx-storage').SyncConflictResult} current
     * @param {import('rxdb/dist/types/rx-storage').SyncConflictResult} newItem
     * @returns {Promise<'overwrite' | 'merge' | 'ignore'>}
     */
    async resolveConflictWrite(current, newItem) {
        if (deepEqual(current.document, newItem.document)) {
            // If the documents are identical, ignore the new item
            return 'ignore';
        }
        // In a real-world scenario, you would implement more complex merge logic here.
        // For this example, we'll arbitrarily decide to keep the new item.
        // This could be based on timestamps, custom merging functions, or user input.
        return 'merge'; // Or 'overwrite' depending on your strategy
    }
};
```

