### Detect Document Equality with RxDB isEqual

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/local-first-future.md

The isEqual function is used internally to detect conflicts or determine if a document needs to be pushed to a remote server. It performs a deep equality check between two documents. For performance in custom conflict handlers, consider checking only specific properties like 'updatedAt' or revision strings.

```javascript
isEqual(a, b) {
    /**
     * isEqual() is used to detect conflicts or to detect if a
     * document has to be pushed to the remote.
     * If the documents are deep equal,
     * we have no conflict.
     * Because deepEqual is CPU expensive,
     * on your custom conflict handler you might only
     * check some properties, like the updatedAt time or revision-strings
     * for better performance.
     */
    return deepEqual(a, b);
}
```

