### Modify Push Response with GraphQL RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication-graphql.md

Enables modification of the response from a push mutation. This is helpful when the server returns more than just conflicting documents, allowing extraction of specific data like conflicts. The modifier receives the raw response and returns the processed data, such as an array of conflicts.

```typescript
import {} from "rxdb";
const replicationState: RxGraphQLReplicationState<RxDocType> = replicateGraphQL(
    {
        collection: myRxCollection,
        url: {/* ... */},
        headers: {/* ... */},
        push: {
            responseModifier: async function (plainResponse) {
                /**
                 * In this example we aggregate the conflicting documents from a response object
                 */
                return plainResponse.conflicts;
            },
        },
        pull: {/* ... */},
        /* ... */
    }
);

```

