### Perform Incremental Upsert Operations in RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-collection.html

The incrementalUpsert method prevents '409 Conflict' errors during rapid upsert operations on the same RxDocument. It behaves similarly to RxDocument.incrementalModify, ensuring that concurrent updates are handled gracefully by queuing them.

```javascript
const docData = {    name: 'Bob', // primary    lastName: 'Kelso'};
myCollection.upsert(docData);
myCollection.upsert(docData);

// Potential conflict here due to parallel updates

// Use incrementalUpsert to avoid conflicts
myCollection.incrementalUpsert(docData);
myCollection.incrementalUpsert(docData);
myCollection.incrementalUpsert(docData);

// Wait for the last upsert to finish
await myCollection.incrementalUpsert(docData);
```

