### Implement RxDB Push Handler on Client

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication-http.md

This client-side code configures the push handler for RxDB replication. It sends an array of change rows to a server endpoint using a POST request with JSON payload. It expects an array of conflicting documents in the JSON response. Dependencies include the `fetch` API.

```typescript
// > client.ts
const replicationState = await replicateRxCollection({
    /* ... */
    push: {
        async handler(changeRows){
            const rawResponse = await fetch('https://localhost/push', {
                method: 'POST',
                headers: {
                    'Accept': 'application/json',
                    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
                },
                body: JSON.stringify(changeRows)
            });
            const conflictsArray = await rawResponse.json();
            return conflictsArray;
        }
    }
    /* ... */
});
```
